Commentary: \‘Lamenting’ or ‘crying for a vision’： spiritual retreat in
  an isolated spot, such as a mountain top.
---
The ‘lamenter’ cries, for he is humbling himself, remembering his
nothingness in the presence of the Great Spirit.
